T*
(Manuscript) Tj
T*
T*
(**Title:** The development of velum coordination in children: a real-time MRI study) Tj
T*
(**Author:** Sean Foley) Tj
T*
(**Date on manuscript:** February 15, 2026) Tj
T*
T*
(1\) Study Summary) Tj
T*
T*
(This manuscript presents an rtMRI study of velum-tongue tip \(TT\) coordination in American) Tj
T*
(English-speaking children \(reported final sample: 7 female speakers, ages 5-15\). The main) Tj
T*
(questions concern developmental patterns in \(i\) velum-TT timing, \(ii\) velum magnitude, \(iii\)) Tj
T*
(velum duration, and \(iv\) timing stability. Stimuli contrast onset, coda, and juncture-geminate) Tj
T*
(nasal contexts in labial/alveolar frames. The key claim is that the two oldest speakers \(age) Tj
T*
(15\) pattern like adults \(onset near-synchrony; coda/geminate earlier velum lowering\), while) Tj
T*
(younger speakers largely show uniformly early velum lowering across conditions. The paper) Tj
T*
(further argues that velum target-to-TT onset lag is more stable than onset lag and may) Tj
T*
(therefore be the more relevant timing relation.) Tj
T*
T*
(2\) Major Issues \(Priority\)) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(1. **Inference is stronger than design supports \(very small, non-independent sample\).**) Tj
T*
(The developmental interpretation is based on seven speakers \(with sibling pairs\), all female,) Tj
T*
(with clear clustering by age but sparse coverage. The sharp "stage shift" claim \(5-14 vs 15\) is) Tj
T*
(plausible but not well identified statistically with this sample structure. At minimum, claims) Tj
T*
(should be reframed as preliminary and exploratory.) Tj
T*
T*
(2. **Statistical independence and pseudoreplication concerns are not fully addressed.**) Tj
T*
(Many token-level observations are modeled, but speaker-level N is very small. This risks) Tj
T*
(overconfident inference from repeated measures when between-speaker evidence is limited. The) Tj
T*
(manuscript should explicitly separate within-speaker effects from speaker-level developmental) Tj
T*
(generalizations.) Tj
T*
T*
(3. **"Stability" is inferred from non-significance in correlation tests.**) Tj
T*
(The argument "no significant correlation => stability" is not sufficient, especially with small) Tj
T*
(per-speaker sample sizes and varying power. A better analysis would use equivalence testing,) Tj
T*
(confidence-interval bounds, or explicit variance-based stability metrics.) Tj
T*
T*
(4. **Multiple testing strategy is under-specified.**) Tj
T*
(Many within-speaker pairwise Wilcoxon comparisons are reported, but there is no clear) Tj
T*
(correction strategy across the family of tests \(and figures use significance stars\). This can) Tj
T*
(inflate false positives.) Tj
T*
T*
(5. **Methodological reporting has reproducibility gaps.**) Tj
T*
(Key details are missing or incomplete: number of usable tokens per condition after exclusions,) Tj
ET
endstream
