(4\) Methods) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(1. **Participant description and dependency structure need clearer handling.**) Tj
T*
(Sibling pairs are included, and one participant is excluded. The manuscript should report) Tj
T*
(exactly how family structure is handled in modeling \(or why it is negligible\).) Tj
T*
T*
(2. **Potential inconsistency in speaker IDs.**) Tj
T*
(The text mentions `Spk7` in ROI description, but participant table lists `Spk5, Spk8, Spk11a,) Tj
T*
(Spk11b, Spk14, Spk15a, Spk15b`. This inconsistency needs correction.) Tj
T*
T*
(3. **ROI and landmark pipeline needs reproducibility metrics.**) Tj
T*
(Provide quantitative reliability checks: repeated ROI placement, intra-/inter-annotator) Tj
T*
(consistency for alignment correction and gestural landmarks, and error statistics.) Tj
T*
T*
(4. **Control variables are limited for timing interpretation.**) Tj
T*
(Speech rate and prosodic variation are likely to affect timing/duration outcomes but are not) Tj
T*
(clearly controlled in primary models.) Tj
T*
T*
(5. **Only low-vowel context is used.**) Tj
T*
(The manuscript acknowledges this limitation, but because intrinsic vowel nasalization can) Tj
T*
(affect velum behavior, this confound should be more central in interpretation.) Tj
